<subSubSection id="C330655BFFA8FF9AFF6E8EEB28B71EAD" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9536D0FFA8FF9AFF6E8EEB28B71EAD" blockId="8.[136,1452,1496,1667]" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA8FF9AFF6E8EEB2C7E1E39" bold="true" box="[189,327,1532,1558]" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">Description</emphasis>
:—Terrestrial or epiphytic succulent plants, of open, shrubby, growth. 
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA8FF9AFB8C8EEA29991E38" box="[1119,1184,1533,1559]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">Stems</emphasis>
up to 20(–30) cm long. 
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA8FF9AFF5B8D362DEF1E15" box="[136,214,1569,1594]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">Leaves</emphasis>
narrowly ovate to obovate; 
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA8FF9AFDC18D362F541E15" box="[530,621,1569,1594]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">margins</emphasis>
with shallow crenations. 
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA8FF9AFC5F8D3729141E15" box="[908,1069,1568,1594]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">Inflorescences</emphasis>
10(–15) cm long, erect to slightly leaning. 
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA8FF9AFF398D532C7F1E71" box="[234,326,1604,1630]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">Flowers</emphasis>
globular in bud, double, 
<quantity id="4CD29B35FFA8FF9AFDB58D532FD91E70" box="[614,736,1604,1631]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.65" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" unit="mm" value="26.5" valueMax="28.0" valueMin="25.0">25–28 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4CD29B35FFA8FF9AFCFA8D522E9A1E70" box="[809,931,1605,1631]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" unit="mm" value="18.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="17.0">17–20 mm</quantity>
in diameter at the widest point, deep metallic purple-red, light green-infused towards lobes; 
<emphasis id="B95EEAC2FFA8FF9AFD5C8D7F2FF31EAD" box="[655,714,1640,1666]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">lobes</emphasis>
light green, subtended by small succulent bracts, campanulate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
